      <section class="femorph-process">
	<h2 class="process-title">Basic FEMORPH Process</h2>

	<div class="scroll-section">

	  <!-- STEP 1 -->
	  <div class="scroll-step slideshow">
	    <div class="scroll-text">
              <h3>1. Collect Geometry Data</h3>
              <p>Geometry data is collected using high-precision tools such as coordinate measuring machines (CMMs) and optical 3D scanners. These produce detailed point clouds or surface meshes for each component.</p>
	    </div>
	    <div class="scroll-media">
              <img src="cmm_rotor.webp" alt="CMM machine">
              <img src="atos.jpg" alt="Optical scanner">
              <img src="cmm_points.png" alt="Raw scan data">
	    </div>
	  </div>

	  <!-- STEP 2 -->
	  <div class="scroll-step">
	    <div class="scroll-text">
              <h3>2. Import into FEMORPH</h3>
              <p>The measurement data is imported into FEMORPH, where it can be analyzed alongside the baseline simulation model.</p>
	    </div>
	    <div class="scroll-media">
              <img src="gui_shiny.png" alt="Importing scan into FEMORPH" class="active">
	    </div>
	  </div>

	  <!-- STEP 3 -->
	  <div class="scroll-step">
	    <div class="scroll-text">
              <h3>3. Align and Compare</h3>
              <p>FEMORPH aligns the measured geometry and baseline model, producing a detailed deviation map that quantifies local shape differences.</p>
	    </div>
	    <div class="scroll-media">
              <img src="pbs_deviation.png" alt="Alignment and deviation visualization", class="active">
	    </div>
	  </div>

	  <!-- STEP 4 -->
	  <div class="scroll-step">
	    <div class="scroll-text">
              <h3>4. Morph the Mesh</h3>
              <p>Robust mesh morphing transfers the measured geometric deviations to the simulation model, eliminating the need for time-consuming remeshing.</p>
	    </div>
	    <div class="scroll-media">
              <video autoplay muted loop playsinline, class="active">
		<source src="turbine_morph.mp4" type="video/mp4">
              </video>
	    </div>
	  </div>

	  <!-- STEP 5 -->
	  <div class="scroll-step">
	    <div class="scroll-text">
              <h3>5. Save the script for automated morphing next data set</h3>
              <p>The steps performed in the GUI are implementing python function calls.  These are recorded into a script for reuse.</p>
	    </div>
	    <div class="scroll-media">
              <img src="tmp.png" alt="Final morphed model and analysis results", class="active">
	    </div>
	  </div>

	</div>
      </section>



